revision.text:
'''Adrian Richard West Room''' (27 September 1933, Melksham – 6 November 2010, Stamford)<ref name=gale>''Contemporary Authors Online'', Gale, 2002; accessed 20 May 2013.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snsbi.org.uk/Nomina.html|title=Society for Name Studies in Britain and Ireland: Nomina|author=Staff|website=Society for Name Studies in Britain and Ireland|accessdate=14 July 2014}}.</ref><ref name=ARdeathnotice>{{cite journal|title=Room Adrian : Obituary|publisher=Stamford Mercury Group (Rutland & Stamford Mercury)|date=12 November 2010}}</ref> was a British [[toponymist]] and [[onomastician]], a Fellow of the [[Royal Geographical Society]]<ref>Cover notes, ''Place-Name Changes Since 1900: A world gazetteer''. London: [[Routledge & Kegan Paul]], 1980. {{ISBN|0710007027}}</ref> and a prolific author of reference works relating primarily to the origins of word and place-names.<ref>[http://catdir.loc.gov/catdir/enhancements/fy0611/2001369116-b.html Contributor biographical information for Brewer's dictionary of modern phrase & fable/compiled by Adrian Room], [[Library of Congress]], 21 May 2013; retrieved 21 May 2013. [https://www.webcitation.org/6Glgdkb2e Archived here.]</ref>
Between 1952 and 1979, Room served in the [[Royal Naval Reserve]], Special Branch, retiring as a Lieutenant Commander.<ref name=gale/> Before becoming a full-time author, he was employed at [[King's College School, Cambridge]], where he taught modern languages and was a senior house master. He later, until 1984, worked as a senior lecturer in Russian for the [[Ministry of Defence (United Kingdom)|British Defence Ministry]].<ref name=AdrRooBookAll>{{cite web|url=http://www.hbcbookalliance.com/Author_Details.aspx?AuthorId=2463|title=Adrian Room|publisher=Book Alliance, [[New Delhi]]|accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref>
