The [[Tuvan People's Republic]] in its short life span went through a number of [[flag]]s. Many typical [[Communist symbolism|communist icon]]s were used such as the [[Hammer and Sickle]] and the [[color red]].
{| class="wikitable" ! class="hintergrundfarbe8" colspan="6" |The flags of the Tuvan People's Republic. |- align="center" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" |[[File:Flag of the Tuvinian Peoples Revolutionary Party.svg|160px|none]] |[[File:Flag of Tannu Tuva (1921-1926).svg|160px|none]] |[[File:Flag of the Tuvan People's Republic (1926-1930).svg|160px|none]] |[[File:Flag of the Tuvan People's Republic (1930-1933).svg|160px|none]] |- class="hintergrundfarbe8" align="center" | 1921 | 1921 to 1926 | 1926 to 1930 | 1930 to 1933 |- |[[File:Flag of the Tuvan People's Republic (1933-1939).svg|160px|none]] |[[File:Flag_of_the_Tuvan_People's_Republic_(1941-1943).svg|160px|none]] |[[File:Flag_of_the_Tuvan_People's_Republic_(1943-1944).svg|160px|none]] |- class="hintergrundfarbe8" align="center" | 1933 to 1941 | 1941 to 1943 | 1943 to 1944 |}
The 1921 flag's inscriptions read, "Flag of the executive committee of the People's Revolutionary Party of Tannu Tuva" (tangnu tiva yin arad un qubisyal tu nam un quriyan u tuy). The 1926-1930 flag started being used after the Constitution of 24 November 1926 and the inscription read, "Tuvan People's Republic" (Bügüde Nayiramdaqu Tuva Arad Ulus). The 1941-1943 flag had the initials of the state ('''T'''ıwa '''A'''rat '''R'''espublik) in gold in canton. The 1943-1944 was just the Cyrillic version ('''Т'''ыва '''А'''рат '''Р'''еспублик).
