{{Infobox mountain | name = Jabal Umm ad Dami | photo = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 1854 | elevation_ref = <ref>[http://www.peakbagger.com/peak.aspx?pid=27957 "Jabal Umm ad Dami" on Peakbagger.com] Retrieved 1 October 2011</ref> | prominence_m = | prominence_ref = | listing = [[List of countries by highest point|Country high point]] | map = Jordan | map_caption = Location of Jabal Umm ad Dami within Jordan (near border with Saudi Arabia) | map_size = 200 | label_position = top | location = [[Aqaba Governorate|Aqaba]], [[Jordan]] | range = | coordinates = {{coord|29|18|30|N|35|25|45|E|type:mountain_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coordinates_ref = | topo = | type = | age = | last_eruption = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = }} '''Jabal Umm ad Dami''', in historic [[Wadi Rum]], is the [[List of countries by highest point|highest mountain]] in [[Jordan]]. Its claimed elevation of 1,854 metres<ref>[http://bubl.ac.uk/org/tacit/TAC/tac47/highjink.htm High Jinks - An update to World Tops and Bottoms] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080327141641/http://bubl.ac.uk/org/tacit/tac/tac47/highjink.htm |date=2008-03-27 }}</ref> is consistent with [[SRTM]] data. It is located at {{coord|29|18|30|N|35|25|45|E|type:mountain}}, near to the border with Saudi Arabia in the [[Aqaba Governorate]] of Jordan.
